The Chronicle Thandeka Moyo-Ndlovu, Health Reporter
ZIMBABWE recorded three more Covid -19 cases yesterday, bringing the total number of cases recorded in the country to 985. According to the Ministry of Health and Child Care three of the new cases were recorded in Manicaland and Mashonaland East provinces. “As at 12 July 2020, Zimbabwe had 985 confirmed cases, including 328 recoveries and 18 deaths,” reads a statement from the Ministry. Bulawayo now has 183 confirmed cases; Matabeleland South has 159 while Matabeleland North has 25 cases. 18 people have succumbed to Covid-19 in the country. @thamamoe